---
/**
 * Privacy Policy Page
 *
 * Covers:
 * - Analytics (Vercel Web Analytics)
 * - SMP Data handling
 * - AI & Data accuracy disclosure
 * - Affiliate tracking
 * - Cookies and local storage
 *
 * @module pages/privacy
 */

import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  meta={{
    title: "Privacy Policy | StackHunt",
    description: "Learn how StackHunt collects, uses, and protects your data. Our privacy practices for analytics, cookies, and affiliate tracking."
  }}
>
  <main class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:text-zinc-100 prose-p:text-zinc-400 prose-a:text-indigo-400 hover:prose-a:text-indigo-300 prose-strong:text-zinc-200 prose-li:text-zinc-400">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p class="lead text-xl text-zinc-400">
        Last updated: January 31, 2026
      </p>

      <p>
        StackHunt ("we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy. We believe SaaS research
        should be transparent, which extends to how we handle your data. This policy explains
        how we collect, use, and safeguard information when you visit stackhunt.com.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>A. Analytics Data (Privacy-First)</h3>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Vercel Web Analytics</strong> to understand site usage. This service
        is designed to be privacy-friendly:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>What it tracks:</strong> Page views, referral sources, device types, and broad geographic regions (Country/City level).</li>
        <li><strong>What it does NOT track:</strong> IP addresses, individual user profiles, or cross-site tracking cookies.</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Fully GDPR and CCPA compliant.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>B. SaaS Management Platform (SMP) Data</h3>
      <p>When you use our interactive tools (e.g., Spend Calculator, Stack Comparison):</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Local Processing:</strong> Inputs regarding team size, budget, and department counts are processed locally in your browser. We do not store this data on our servers unless you explicitly create an account and save a "Stack."</li>
        <li><strong>Aggregated Insights:</strong> We may collect anonymous, aggregated telemetry (e.g., "The average user compares Trello vs. Asana") to improve our research algorithms.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>C. Voting & Interaction</h3>
      <p>To ensure the integrity of our voting system (upvotes/downvotes):</p>
      <ul>
        <li>We collect a hashed browser fingerprint and a hashed IP address.</li>
        <li><strong>Hashing:</strong> These identifiers are encrypted via a one-way hash before storage. We cannot reverse-engineer them to identify you personally. They exist solely to prevent vote manipulation.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>D. Cookies & Local Storage</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Security tokens (via Cloudflare) to verify you are human.</li>
        <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> We save your "My Stack" selections and UI preferences (Dark Mode) directly on your device. This data never leaves your browser.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. AI & Data Accuracy Disclosure</h2>

      <p>StackHunt is a programmatic research platform.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>AI Generation:</strong> Our content, including pricing tables, feature summaries, and "Pros/Cons," is synthesized using Artificial Intelligence (Gemini 2.0 Flash) based on publicly available data.</li>
        <li><strong>Accuracy:</strong> While we employ rigorous validation pipelines, AI can make mistakes. We cannot guarantee the accuracy of pricing or feature data. Always verify details on the vendor's official website before making a purchase decision.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Affiliate Disclosure (How We Make Money)</h2>

      <p>StackHunt is a participant in various affiliate programs (including Impact, PartnerStack, and others).</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Links:</strong> When you click a link to a software tool on our site, we may earn a commission from that vendor.</li>
        <li><strong>No Bias:</strong> Our "Fit Scores" and search rankings are generated algorithmically based on feature matching and semantic relevance. Affiliate partnerships do not influence a tool's ranking or score.</li>
        <li><strong>Tracking:</strong> Clicking an affiliate link may set a third-party cookie on your device by the merchant to track the referral.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        For more details, see our{' '}
        <a href="/disclosure" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>

      <p>We use the limited data we collect to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Maintain the functionality and security of the website.</li>
        <li>Prevent fraud and spam in our voting system.</li>
        <li>Analyze aggregate trends to determine which tools to research next.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Retained for up to 12 months in aggregated form.</li>
        <li><strong>Vote Records:</strong> Hashed identifiers are retained indefinitely to maintain the integrity of the total vote counts.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>

      <p>
        Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data (access,
        deletion, correction). However, since StackHunt collects almost no Personally Identifiable
        Information (PII), we likely hold no data that can be directly linked to you.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you have questions or wish to exercise your rights regarding any account data you
        may have saved, please contact us.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>

      <p>
        We may update this policy as our platform evolves. Significant changes will be noted
        by the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>

      <p>For legal inquiries or privacy concerns:</p>
      <p>
        Email:{' '}
        <a href="mailto:privacy@stackhunt.com" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">
          privacy@stackhunt.com
        </a>
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8" />

      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500">
        This policy is effective as of January 31, 2026.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
